    "attributes": {
        "action": "Work with the devolved governments to create UK-wide Civic Curriculum",
        "additional_details": "We think Britain\u2019s unity depends on shared civic values. Devolved education means children in different parts of the UK may learn different histories and civic duties, risking division. We think a UK-wide civic curriculum would strengthen social cohesion for future generations.",
        "background": "We think Britain\u2019s strength comes from shared civic values & understanding of our democracy. We think a UK-wide civic curriculum with clear national standards would ensure pupils learn the same core history, principles & responsibilities, building pride in British identity while respecting diversity",
